description:
&lt;p&gt;Whittington Health trust are looking for Sonographers to join their team. The bank worker will act as clinical specialist for ultrasound services, and in co-operation with other services and Superintendent Sonographer, contribute to the effective and efficient running of the Imaging Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Main Duties will include but are not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act independently in the assessment of referrals for Ultrasound examinations, taking full responsibility for the justification of general Ultrasound examinations. Supervise Sonographers in this process if required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a high level of expertise in the safe operation of Ultrasound equipment and manage faults effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To comply with and contribute to the implementation of departmental and professional policies and procedures such as:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health +Safety including risk assessment and COSHH&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ALARA principles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality Assurance Program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical Effectiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical Audit    &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be able to exercise personal responsibility and make decisions in complex&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and unpredictable circumstances e.g. Prioritising patients according to clinical&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;need in an ultrasound and radiological situation.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To work as part of a team within the Imaging Department and the wider Trust environment to ensure effective communication and delivery of care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To work in a team under challenging circumstances maintaining a calm and collaborative manner at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To raise issues appropriately and face to face with relevant individuals to resolve conflict keeping the organisational iCARE behaviours uppermost.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential Requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HCPC Registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 months NHS experience in a similar role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel you have the skills for this role please apply today.&lt;/p&gt;
